CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 29, 1946, pg. 22, reads: "From Higher Institutions - Having completed their training in institutions of higher learning, these students are prepared to take over the job of teaching the younger generation... Shown at the left are five young women who received Master's degrees from the School of Applied Social Sciences at the University of Pittsburgh.  They are, left to right: Miss Genevieve Howard, Miss Alberta W. Brown, Miss Jean Williams, Miss Marilyn Duncan and Miss [illegible] Womack..."
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh graduates Genevieve Howard, Alberta W. Brown, Jean Williams, Marilyn Duncan, and Ms Womack, posed with diplomas in front of Cathedral of Learning, Oakland
